    <briefdescription>
<para>Container for System instances within a game loop pass. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1SystemRegistry" kindref="compound">SystemRegistry</ref> manages a collection of Systems that execute together within a single pass of the game loop. It provides type-safe registration, lookup, and iteration over Systems.</para>
<para>## Ownership</para>
<para>The registry owns all registered Systems via `std::unique_ptr`. Systems are destroyed when the registry is destroyed.</para>
<para>## Type-Safe Access</para>
<para>Systems can be retrieved by type using `getSystem&lt;T&gt;()`, enabling inter-system communication when necessary.</para>
<para>Example: ```cpp <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1SystemRegistry" kindref="compound">SystemRegistry</ref> registry;</para>
<para>// Add systems registry.add&lt;Move2DSystem&gt;(gameWorld); registry.add&lt;CollisionSystem&gt;(gameWorld);</para>
<para>// Check for system if (registry.hasSystem&lt;CollisionSystem&gt;()) { auto* collision = registry.getSystem&lt;CollisionSystem&gt;(); }</para>
<para>// Iterate all systems for (auto&amp; system : registry.systems()) { system-&gt;update(ctx); } ```</para>
